# validate-gate wiring rule

Use `signalos validate-gate --gate G<n> [--wave W<n>]` before treating a gate
artifact as passed.

- A missing artifact is a HALT failure.
- A missing or draft signature is a HALT failure.
- A signature hash mismatch is a HALT failure.
- A missing audit row is a HALT failure.
- If `--wave` is provided, the audit row must carry the same normalized wave id.
